Epic 4: Predict the Best Crop Based on Given Parameters
Introduction

The Crop Prediction module is an important component of the OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization System. It utilizes a trained Logistic Regression machine learning model to predict the most suitable crop based on soil nutrients and environmental conditions. This module enables farmers to make informed crop selection decisions, leading to improved agricultural productivity and sustainable farming practices.

Objective

The primary objective of this module is to recommend the most suitable crop by analyzing soil nutrient levels and climatic conditions using a trained machine learning model.

Input Parameters

The prediction model requires the following input parameters:

Nitrogen (N)
Phosphorous (P)
Potassium (K)
Temperature (°C)
Humidity (%)
pH Value
Rainfall (mm)

These parameters are collected from the user through the application interface.

Prediction Process

The prediction process consists of the following steps:

The user enters soil and environmental parameters.
The application validates the input values.
The trained Logistic Regression model is loaded using the Pickle library.
The model processes the input values.
The predicted numerical label is converted back into the corresponding crop name using the Label Encoder.
The recommended crop is displayed to the user.
Machine Learning Model

The Logistic Regression algorithm is used as the prediction model because it provides efficient classification performance for the crop recommendation dataset. The trained model is stored as logistic_model.pkl, allowing predictions without retraining the model each time.

Sample Input
Parameter	Value
Nitrogen	90
Phosphorous	42
Potassium	43
Temperature	20.8 °C
Humidity	82%
pH	6.5
Rainfall	202.9 mm
Sample Output

Recommended Crop: Rice

Benefits
Provides quick and accurate crop recommendations.
Assists farmers in selecting suitable crops.
Improves agricultural productivity.
Supports sustainable farming practices.
Reduces the risk of inappropriate crop selection.
Enables data-driven agricultural decision-making.
Applications
Smart Agriculture
Precision Farming
Crop Recommendation Systems
Agricultural Decision Support Systems
AI-Based Farming Applications
Conclusion

The Crop Prediction module successfully predicts the most suitable crop using soil nutrients and environmental parameters. By leveraging the trained Logistic Regression model, the OptiCrop system provides accurate crop recommendations that help farmers improve productivity, optimize resource utilization, and support sustainable agricultural development.